{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6ac95eb-c911-43d5-837e-8720b67e313f","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me help you directly instead.\n\nHere are the recommended tools for post-mortem dump analysis:\n\n**Cross-platform (recommended):**\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-your.dmp>\n```\n\nUseful commands inside `dotnet-dump analyze`:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Print the last exception |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\n**On Windows:** WinDbg with the SOS extension is the most powerful option.\n\n**On Linux:** `lldb` with the SOS plugin also works.\n\n**Typical investigation flow:**\n1. `clrthreads` — find the thread that crashed (look for exception info)\n2. `setthread <id>` — switch to that thread\n3. `clrstack` — see the managed call stack\n4. `pe` — print the exception details (type, message, inner exceptions)\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` in this environment and walk through the analysis with you? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2974d9e7-fce1-4b18-ae02-43c32b110825","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET crash dump file (.dmp) and wants to analyze it to find the root cause. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the `dump-collect` skill is not appropriate here. Let me help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.\n\nI should provide guidance on how to analyze the dump using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, `lldb`, or `windbg`. Let me check what tools are available in the environment first, but more importantly, I should ask where the dump file is located.\n\n\nSince we're likely on Linux, I'll focus on `dotnet-dump analyze` or `lldb` with the SOS debugging extension as the primary tools for analyzing the dump. Let me ask the user for the dump file path so I can help them get started with the analysis.","outputTokens":701,"requestId":"980D:24F9C3:C0D739:E1FD09:69F407B8"},"id":"1ae9a0f4-6459-4e34-af8b-34aceb80c77c","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:54:16.743Z","parentId":"7b962e2c-4172-493d-95fa-da04d2c98840"}
